            My noble friend does not answer the point that to keep the worker in the dark&#x2014;because that is what it is&#x2014;as to his proper written particulars of his employment terms in itself damages the employment relationship. Of course, from the employer's point of view, it may not be much damage, and that is the point of view the Government have espoused. Will the Government think again, from its roots, on this matter of sanction in Section 12 of the <a href="/acts/employment-rights-act-1996">Employment Rights Act</a>?
